article.headline: Boise State 82, Idaho 68
article.story: MOSCOW, Idaho (AP) -- Junior guard Koby Karl scored 25 points as Boise State beat in-state rival Idaho 82-68 Saturday at Cowan Spectrum. Karl was 8-for-14 from the floor against the Vandals, including a 6-for-8 clip from beyond the 3-point arc. Boise State (10-9, 3-5 Western Athletic Conference) won its fifth straight game in the series between the schools, which now stands 42-37 in the Broncos' favor. The loss was the eighth straight for Idaho (3-14, 0-6), which hasn't won since defeating North Dakota State 76-71 on Dec. 21. The Vandals were led by Tanoris Shepard with 23 points. David Dubois added 14 points. Boise State reeled off a 14-0 run to take a commanding 17-4 lead with 11:40 to play before halftime. Shepard hit a basket to break a 7-minute scoreless drought, and the Vandals cut their deficit to single digits when Matt Forge made a 3-pointer at the 9:53 mark. The Broncos had a 9-0 run, and extended their lead to 18 points before taking a 35-20 lead at halftime. Idaho's Brett Ledbetter hit five consecutive 3-pointers in 3:10 to cut Boise State's 17-point second-half lead to 48-44 with 12:52 to play. He finished with 17 points The Broncos put together a 10-2 run that extended their lead to 58-46 with 10:22 to play. Idaho closed to within 74-68 on a basket by Shepard with 1:10 remaining. But the Vandals would get no closer, as Boise State converted 6 of 8 free throws over the game's final 57.5 seconds and an open-court dunk by Kareem Lloyd with 4 seconds left. Eric Lane added 18 points for the Broncos, who made good on 28 of 49 field-goal attempts (57.1 percent). Idaho hit 19 of 32 of its second-half shots (59.4 percent) after going 8-for-31 (25.8 percent) in the first half.
